[05:26.43]Young Stamford looked rather strangely at me over his wine-glass. "You don't know Sherlock Holmes yet," he said; "perhaps you would not care for him as a constant companion." 
小斯坦弗从酒杯上很惊诧地望着我，他说:“你还不知道夏洛克·福尔摩斯吧，否则你也许会不愿意和他作一个长年相处的伙伴哩。” 

[05:39.28]"Why, what is there against him?"  "Oh, I didn't say there was anything against him. He is a little queer（奇怪的） in his ideas -- an enthusiast in some branches of science. As far as I know he is a decent fellow enough." 
